description.narrative: (Philippines): The five-year Mindanao Youth for Development activity will increase equitable access to education and improve life skills and employability for vulnerable out-of-school youth (OSY) in selected conflict and crisis-affected areas of Mindanao. This will be accomplished through a set of interrelated components, that: increase youth's equitable access to education in crisis and conflict environments through the Department of Education's Alternative Learning System (ALS); boost out-of-school youth employability by providing equitable access to relevant education and skills training; strengthen the capacity of local government units, communities, and stakeholders to deliver education and training service delivery for out-of-school youth.With FY 2015 funds, the MYDev will continue to strengthen the capacities of local governments, communities, and other stakeholders to improve education service delivery and increase OSY access to relevant education. Close to 20,000 vulnerable out-of-school youth will benefit from U.S. assistance.
